## What I Learned:
- HTTP is the foundation of data communication on the web
- HTTPS adds encryption via TLS/SSL to secure communication
- HTTP methods: GET (retrieve), POST (create), PUT (update), DELETE (remove)
- Status codes: 2xx success, 3xx redirection, 4xx client errors, 5xx server errors
- Common request headers: Host, User-Agent, Cookie
- Common response headers: Set-Cookie, Cache-Control, Content-Type
- Cookies help servers remember who you are

